definitions.definition: To make final or firm ; to finish or complete .
examples: As soon as we get the plane tickets, we'll finalize our reservations with the hotel.

definitions.definition: To prepare (an object) for garbage collection by calling its finalizer .

main_definition: ( transitive ) To make final or firm ; to finish or complete .
secondary_definitions: ( transitive , computing , programming ) To prepare (an object) for garbage collection by calling its finalizer .
